messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, ma'am. There's a house on fire on Southeast 27th Street.
Southeast 27th Street?
Yeah.
Can you give me a more specific location on Southeast 27th Street?
Um, I don't know.
Okay, what's your address?
I don't know the address here, but it's off Lakewood Avenue.
Okay, please hold while I transfer you to the fire department.
Okay.
There's a fire on Southeast 27th Street.
Yes, ma'am. I don't know if anybody is inside.
Can you give me a better address with a cross street?
It's off Lakewood Avenue.
Do you know if there's anybody in the house?
I don't know. I was driving by and I just saw it on fire. There are three or four cars in the driveway. The whole front porch is engulfed.
What's your name and phone number?
Hey, I don't know if anyone is in the house. I was just driving by and saw it.
Okay, is the fire just on the front porch or spreading to the rest of the house?
It's starting to burn the whole roof now. It's getting really intense.
Alright, help is on the way. Are you still there?
Yes, there are some cars in the front yard. I don't see anyone outside or any neighbors around.
Can you see anyone running out of the house?
There are some people coming out now.
Can you see if anyone else is still in the house?
I just saw one person come out; he said there are kids inside.
Okay, stay on the phone with me. Are there children inside the house?
Yes, but he ran off somewhere. The house is almost half engulfed.
Did the person who ran out say how many kids are inside?
He mentioned a couple of kids.
Please ask him if there are any more children or people inside.
He just said there’s only one person inside now. I don't know if it's a child.
Is the fire department there yet?
Yes, they just arrived. I still see flames catching on the trees and everything.
Okay, they should be handling it now. Thank you for calling. Stay safe.
Thank you.
